SAN FRANCISCO - Facebook Inc said on Wednesday it was expanding the jobs section on its social network, as it looks to compete in a market dominated by Microsoft Corp’s LinkedIn. The expansion marks the tool’s international rollout a year after it was launched in the United States and Canada. READ: Facebook to use postcards to verify identities Facebook also said it plans to invest about $1 billion (R11,5 billion) in its teams, technology and new programmes in 2018. eNCA